    given-names: Sumit
    affiliation: H2S Hackathon 2026 Submission
repository-code: "https://github.com/sumit0202/election-assistant"
url: "https://github.com/sumit0202/election-assistant"
abstract: >-
  CivicGuide is a non-partisan, multilingual, voice-friendly assistant that
  helps citizens understand the election process — eligibility, voter
  registration, polling logistics, voting machines, and post-poll counting.
  It integrates Google Gemini (via Vertex AI), Maps Platform, YouTube Data
  API, Cloud Translation, and ICS calendar export, runs on Google Cloud
  Run, and ships with a 3-layer fallback chain (FAQ → LLM → graceful
  degradation) so the service stays useful even when upstream LLM quotas
  are exceeded.
